# Changelog  
All notable changes to this project will be documented here.

## [2025-11-08]  
### Added  
- API Gateway (Kong OSS) service defined.  
- Malware scanning with ClamAV integrated.  
- Admin UIs for DB and Redis added behind CF Access.  
### Changed  
- Centralised DB/cache strategy for all services.  
### Removed  
- Per-container databases on each service host.  
Reviewed-by: reagents 2025-11-09T04:02Z (docker compose -f compose.orchestrator.yml config)

## [2025-11-09]  
### Changed  
- Synced Infisical prod secrets from `.workspace/.env` via `infisical --domain https://vault.freqkflag.co/api secrets set --file .workspace/.env --env prod --path / --token <service-token>` (2025-11-09T07:12:55Z).  

## [2025-11-10]  
### Added  
- Implemented dedicated Cursor agents for discovery, compose linting, secrets audits, deployments, security, API gateways, documentation, reviews, releases, and automation workflows (see `.cursor/agents/*_agent.py`).  
- Introduced `.cursor/agents/utils.py` plus `scripts/agents/selftest_agents.py` to keep command wrappers consistent.  
### Changed  
- Documented the agent suite and invocation flow across `AGENTS.md`, `PROJECT_PLAN.md`, and `infra-build-plan.md`.  
- Hardened `nodes/vps.host/compose.yml` with shared service defaults, explicit Traefik labels, and health checks to satisfy compose-engineer validation ahead of agent execution.  
- Populated `INFISICAL_WEBHOOK_URL` placeholders in environment templates so automation agents can emit webhook events outside dry runs.  
- Deployment runner now emits webhook events for every step, includes target-aware health checks, and performs rollback notifications on failure.  
